  • Method Details

    • decodeUtf8

      public static void decodeUtf8(byte[] bytes, int offset, int length, StringBuilder output)
      Decodes utf8 bytes into a reusable StringBuilder object. Going through a builder has benefits on JDK8, but is (significantly) slower when decoding ascii on JDK13.

    • decodeBase64

      public static RepeatedByte decodeBase64(int expectedSize, String... parts)
      Parses binary data from base64 encoded String segments. Byte arrays are stored very inefficiently in class files, so it is better to store binary data (e.g. descriptors) in string form and parse it at runtime. String literals are limited to 64K, so the data may be split into multiple parts.
      Parameters:
      expectedSize - size hint for allocating the initial array
      parts - binary parts encoded as base64 strings
      Returns:
      the byte representation of the descriptor

    • hash32

      public static int hash32(CharSequence value)
      Hash code for JSON field name lookup. Any changes need to be synchronized between FieldUtil::hash32 and ProtoUtil::hash32.
